reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Use with both computers
reviews.reviewText: I work from home as a temporary employee for different departments within the University I retired from 10 years ago whenever they need me to fill in for Research Administrators on leave or while replacing a promoted or terminated employee. I have a Lenova Thinkpad with Dock as well as my personal Lenova touchscreen Ideapad. I was using a usb set up hooked to a displayport my son had given me to work with dual hdmi monitors but over the past couple of years it became finicky and took time to reconfigure displays.I bought this little Dock for my personal laptop but since the Thinkpad had a USB-C, decided to retire the Work Dock and use this for both computers. It seamlessly moves from each which are stacked on a stand, and coupled with the dual monitor stand I also bought myself at Christmas, has provided the easiest workstation I've had for the last 10 years!!! I use the USB port for the little keyboard/mouse doohicky and still have an extra USB for my flash drives. I'm getting too old to work (LOL) so my only complaint is that I didn't do this 10 years ago!!! I did have to buy a usb C male to female extender as the cord is very short but I did let it "float on air" for the days to get the extension. All in all...I love it!

I bought this for my daughter as her new laptop didn’t have and USB ports that is needed for school. It works great! No issues, light weight, and is great for all her devices needed in order to do school work.
Te da bastante productividad al poder conectar 3 dispositivos al mismo tiempo, puedes cargar la Mac.

Don’t really need all the usb ports but love that it comes with sd slot and usb c. Like that it plugs in to be right against my mac but sometimes falls out (and I need to take off my case to make sure it actually connects). Still great and glad I got it.
